Nobody never said anything for a whi le; then the young man hove a si gh
and says:

“Alas !”

“What ’re you al as s in’ about?” says the bald head.

“To think I should have lived to be leading such a life, and be
de gra ded down into such company .” And he begun to wi pe the corner of
