shoes nor stir rup s, and resting their hands on their thi gh s easy and
comfort able —there must ’a’ been twenty of them —and every lady with
a lovely complex ion, and perfectly beautiful, and looking just like
a gang of real sure - enough que en s, and dressed in clothes that cost
mi llions of dollars, and just lit tered with di am on ds. It was a powerful
fine si ght; I never see anything so lovel y. And then one by one they
got up and stood, and went a- wea ving around the ring so gentle and
