and made his bow and d anced off to the dressing- room, and everybody
just a- howling with pleasure and astonishment.

Then the ringmaster he see how he had been foo led, and he was the
sick est ringmaster you ever see, I reckon. Why, it was one of his
own men ! He had got up that joke all out of his own head, and never
let on to nobody. Well, I felt she epi sh enough to be took in so, but
I wouldn’t ’a’ been in that ring master ’s place, not for a thousand
