“‘ She t de do ’ .’

“She never done it; jis’ stood da h, kin er smi lin’ up at me. It make me
ma d; en I says ag’in, mighty lou d, I says:

“‘ Doan’ you hear me? She t de do ’ !”

“She jis stood de same way, kin er smi lin’ up. I was a- bil in ’! I says:

“‘I lay I make you min e!’

“E n wid dat I fet ch ’ her a sla p side de head dat son t her a- sp ra w lin ’.
Den I went into de yuther room, en ’uz gone ’bout ten minut es; en when
