“A l as, al as, our poor brother — gone, and we never got to see him; oh,
it’s too, too hard !”

Then he turns around, blubber ing, and makes a lot of idio tic signs to
the duke on his hands, and blamed if he didn’t drop a carpet- bag and
bust out a- crying. If they warn’t the beat en est lo t, them two frauds,
that ever I struck.

Well, the men gathered around and sympa thi zed with them, and said all
sorts of kind things to them, and carried their carpet-bag s up the
