and didn’t find nothing, what would she think of me? B lame it, I says,
I might get hunted up and j ai le d; I’d better lay low and keep dark,
and not write at all; the thing’s awful mixed now; trying to better
it, I’ve wor s ened it a hundred times, and I wish to goodness I’d just
let it alone, dad fetch the whole business !

They buried him, and we come back home, and I went to watching fac es
