“Why, Sally, I couldn’t miss him along the road —you know that.”

“But oh, dear, dear, what will S is say ! He must ’a’ com e! You must
’a’ missed him. He —”

“Oh, don’t distre ss me any more’n I’m already distre s sed. I don’t know
what in the world to make of it. I’m at my wit’s end, and I don’t mind
ac knowle dg ing ’t I’m right down scared. But there’s no hope that he’s
