in it but some old rusty pla ye d- out ho es and sp ad es and picks and a
crippled pl ow. The mat ch went out, and so did w e, and shoved in the
sta ple again, and the door was locked as good as ever. Tom was joy ful.
He says:

“Now we’re all right. We’ll dig him out. It ’ll take about a week !”

Then we started for the house, and I went in the back door —you only
have to pull a buck skin lat ch- string, they don’t fast en the door s— but
that warn’t rom an tical enough for Tom Sawy er; no way would do him but
