it would work, and it just worked noble ; when Jim bit into it it most
m ashed all his teeth out; and there warn’t ever anything could ’a’
worked better. Tom said so himself. Jim he never let on but what it
was only just a piece of rock or something like that that’s always
getting into brea d, you know; but after that he never bit into nothing
but what he jab bed his for k into it in three or four places first.

And whilst we was a-standing there in the di m mi sh light, here comes a
couple of the h ounds bul ging in from under Jim’s bed; and they kept on
piling in till there was eleven of them, and there warn’t hardly room
in there to get your brea th. By jings, we forgot to fast en that
