door too. Then he went to work on the nigger, coa x ing him and pe tting
him, and asking him if he’d been imagin ing he saw something again. He
raised up, and blin ked his eyes around, and says:

“ Mars Sid, you’ll say I’s a fool, but if I didn’t b’lieve I see most a
