1. Here a cap tive heart bu sted.

2. Here a poor prisoner, for s ook by the world and
friends, fre tted his sorrow ful life.

3. Here a lonely heart bro ke, and a worn spirit went
to its rest, after thirty-seven years of sol itary cap ti v ity.

4. Here, home less and friend less, after thirty-seven
years of bitter cap ti v ity, peri shed a noble stranger,
natural son of Louis X IV.

Tom’s voice trem bled whilst he was reading them, and he most broke
