cross- purposes, the wonderful chains of events, working through
gener ations, and leading to the most ou tr é resul ts, it would make all
fi ction with its con venti on al ities and foreseen conclusions most sta le
and un prof it able.”

“And yet I am not convinced of it,” I answered. “The cases which come
to light in the papers are, as a rule, bald enough, and vul gar enough.
We have in our police repor ts reali s m pushed to its extreme lim it s, and
yet the result is, it must be conf essed, neither fascin ating nor
arti stic .”

