reali stic effe ct ,” remarked Holmes. “This is wanting in the police
repor t, where more stre ss is la id, perhaps, upon the plat itud es of the
magi str ate than upon the detail s, which to an obser ver contain the
v ital ess ence of the whole matter. D ep end upon it, there is nothing so
unnatural as the common place.”

I smiled and shook my head. “I can quite understand your thinking so,”
