IV. THE BO SC O M B E V AL LE Y M Y ST ER Y


We were seated at breakfast one morning, my wife and I, when the maid
brought in a telegra m. It was from Sherlock Holmes and ran in this way:

“Have you a couple of days to spar e? Have just been wi red for from the
